venue.name: Owls & PussyCat Art Cafe by Kokopelli

tip.text: Merdeka - sampai 6.40pm, dapat meja dan siap order 7.40pm (2x line up - meja 1x, order 1x). Yg sedap - udang butter, sotong tepung, scallop halia. Malangnya, ikan tak fresh. Dessert - aiskrim potong.

venue.name: Medan Ikan Bakar Muara Sg. Duyung

tip.text: Service and the bed...so comfy! The view from the room was awesome too
My kids loved it esp when they get to feed cute lemurs and touch and carry a small gibbon. The safari tram ride was fun, the guide was funny. Some rare animals in here and the shows were fun too 👍
Bawa co-driver as parking susah. Bayar kompaun di Level 3. Kaunter bayaran and kaunter rayuan sebelah-menyebelah (untuk minta diskaun) 👍
The seafood chowder was good, served hot. I also had the fish & chip (red snapper) which was good too. I like that the place serves smaller sized meals. For dessert - mudpie was yummy!
Get card for tourist offers 10% discount - pay normal price & 10% of amount will be credited into the card that can be utilised for next purchase. Claim your VAT too (about 11%), min 90.16€.
Book the end room/apt, nice sea view. Well furnished, shower water pressure good. Pool a bit small, if not go to the beach. Careful though during high tide, steep gradient. Good for family.
Great place to see bats hanging :-)
Nice view after rain
Bring your own pen and ensure photocopy all relevant documents like IC etc before coming. If not, 20 sen per copy. Well, at least they allow us to make photocopy

tip.text: The road is small and zigzag but the view is awesome. Was told it's even more beautiful around May/June when the paddy is ripe
